<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Apply Guardrails at Runtime on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/ai/4-splunk-agent-observability/8-apply-guardrails/</link><description>Recent content in Apply Guardrails at Runtime on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/ai/4-splunk-agent-observability/8-apply-guardrails/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Add Agent Control to the App</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/ai/4-splunk-agent-observability/8-apply-guardrails/1-add-agent-control/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/ai/4-splunk-agent-observability/8-apply-guardrails/1-add-agent-control/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;First, wire the Agent Control SDK into the app: add the configuration, install the packages,
and register the controllable steps.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
&lt;header class="exercise__bar"&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-label"&gt;Exercise&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-divider" aria-hidden="true"&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-title"&gt;Add Agent Control&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__panel"&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__body"&gt;
&lt;section class="step"&gt;
&lt;div class="step__num"&gt;1&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;header class="step__head"&gt;&lt;p class="step__title"&gt;Set up the environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="step__body"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Change into the agent controls folder:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;cd&lt;/span&gt; ~/workshop/healthcare-assistant/4-app-with-controls&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;
&lt;section class="step"&gt;
&lt;div class="step__num"&gt;2&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;header class="step__head"&gt;&lt;p class="step__title"&gt;Create a Galileo Agent Controls Config Map&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="step__body"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Run the following command to create a Kubernetes config map, which the application will use to
configure Galileo Agent Controls:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Define Controls in the Console</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/ai/4-splunk-agent-observability/8-apply-guardrails/2-define-controls/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/ai/4-splunk-agent-observability/8-apply-guardrails/2-define-controls/</guid><description>&lt;div class="callout callout--warning"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path d="M10.29 3.86 1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0z"/&gt;&lt;line x1="12" y1="9" x2="12" y2="13"/&gt;&lt;line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;TODO&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;Confirm which organization will be used for the workshop.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The app now &lt;em&gt;registers&lt;/em&gt; its controllable steps, but it&amp;rsquo;s the Galileo console where you
&lt;em&gt;define the rules&lt;/em&gt;: which steps are governed, what condition triggers them, and whether a
match should block or steer.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Test the Controls</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/ai/4-splunk-agent-observability/8-apply-guardrails/3-test-controls/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/ai/4-splunk-agent-observability/8-apply-guardrails/3-test-controls/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;With the controls defined, run the app and trigger them. You&amp;rsquo;ll see the block and steer
